1
00:00:12,979 --> 00:00:15,777
At least Jarod could have led us
to a place near the Strip...

2
00:00:15,849 --> 00:00:17,783
then I could have
hit the craps table.

3
00:00:17,851 --> 00:00:21,617
[Clears Throat] Well, hit this instead:
single malt, like you asked for.

4
00:00:21,688 --> 00:00:24,452
And you're forgetting something.
Jarod didn't lead us here.

5
00:00:24,524 --> 00:00:27,550
His friend told him to stay here
in an e-mail I intercepted.

6
00:00:27,627 --> 00:00:32,394
- He's been compromised this time,
and he's gonna walk right into our hands.
- My hands.

7
00:00:32,465 --> 00:00:37,164
- Now go to your room.
- Oh, this is my room. Our room.
This is the honeymoon suite.

8
00:00:37,237 --> 00:00:40,968
- Not even after four of these.
- Oh, no, no. Miss Parker, it's perfect.

9
00:00:41,041 --> 00:00:44,568
Why do you think Sydney and Lyle
are coming tomorrow? If Jarod came here...

10
00:00:44,644 --> 00:00:48,410
and he saw a woman and three men
on the register, well, 
he'd- he'd know we're here.

11
00:00:48,481 --> 00:00:50,642
This way, if-
if you and I pretend...

12
00:00:50,717 --> 00:00:53,311
to be the honeymoon couple,
well, he'd be none the wiser.

13
00:00:55,722 --> 00:00:58,748
- This was your idea.
- Yeah.

14
00:00:58,825 --> 00:01:01,817
I mean, it's a good one, isn't it?
Nobody'd believe you and Syd.

15
00:01:01,895 --> 00:01:04,261
He's- He's middle-aged,
and he's Flemish.

16
00:01:04,330 --> 00:01:08,528
And you, you're young and- unless you think
that you'd rather room with Lyle.

17
00:01:08,601 --> 00:01:11,092
Centre's a sick place but-
but your own brother?

18
00:01:13,239 --> 00:01:15,605
Relax, Romeo.
That's as far as I go.

19
00:01:15,675 --> 00:01:18,872
Take first watch. Anybody pulls into
that parking lot, send up a flare.

20
00:01:18,945 --> 00:01:21,004
- Okay.
- Broots?

21
00:01:21,081 --> 00:01:23,606
Fall asleep,
it'll be a hell of a wedding night.

22
00:01:34,894 --> 00:01:36,885
[No Audible Music]

23
00:01:43,736 --> 00:01:46,728
[Bird Chirping In Distance]

24
00:01:48,308 --> 00:01:50,299
[Sighs]

25
00:01:55,381 --> 00:01:58,612
[Murmurs, Clears Throat]

26
00:02:11,998 --> 00:02:14,933
- [Gasps]
- [Sighs]

27
00:02:15,001 --> 00:02:17,902
[Jarod Narrating]
Welcome to Sin City- Las Vegas, Nevada.

28
00:02:17,971 --> 00:02:21,998
A Pretender could win big here-
some other Pretender.

29
00:02:22,075 --> 00:02:24,703
I've been rolling nothing
but snake eyes.

30
00:02:24,777 --> 00:02:29,043
I should be having some fun in the sun,
and all I got is... frostbite.

31
00:02:29,115 --> 00:02:32,414
- They say luck is a lady. 
That must be good luck.
- [Shivering]

32
00:02:32,485 --> 00:02:36,251
- Bad luck is definitely a man, 
and he dresses funny.
- [Teeth Chattering]

33
00:02:36,322 --> 00:02:39,382
Argyle tried to sell me to the Centre
a couple of years back.

34
00:02:39,459 --> 00:02:41,393
Last year he almost got me killed.

35
00:02:41,461 --> 00:02:44,225
- [Sneezes]
- Why should this year be any different?

36
00:02:44,297 --> 00:02:47,266
- [Whimpers]
- Some days it doesn't pay 
to answer your e-mail.

37
00:02:48,601 --> 00:02:51,729
[Man Narrating]
There are Pretenders among us.

38
00:02:51,804 --> 00:02:53,738
[Jarod]
I was taken from my family.

39
00:02:53,806 --> 00:02:57,367
Thirty-six hours and he's already demonstrating
more talent than any of our others.

40
00:02:57,443 --> 00:03:00,844
How many people died
because of what I thought up?

41
00:03:00,914 --> 00:03:04,350
Since I broke out, I've spent 
every moment searching for my past.

42
00:03:04,417 --> 00:03:06,612
[Miss Parker]
He's a Pretender-

43
00:03:06,686 --> 00:03:09,450
A genius who can become
anyone that he wants to be.

44
00:03:09,522 --> 00:03:12,252
- The Centre wants him alive.
- Preferably.

45
00:03:12,325 --> 00:03:15,260
- [Miss Parker] He defends the weak and abused.
- [Jarod] Life's a gift.

46
00:03:27,040 --> 00:03:29,508
- You a doctor?
- I am today.

47
00:03:36,149 --> 00:03:38,845
[Jarod Narrating]
Look at me. Some genius.

48
00:03:38,918 --> 00:03:41,682
I wish I could pretend myself
into some longjohns.

49
00:03:41,754 --> 00:03:47,021
But in my own defense, this all started
when Argyle decided to become a Pretender.

50
00:03:47,093 --> 00:03:50,654
As usual, his mouth was writing checks
his brain couldn't cash.

51
00:03:52,699 --> 00:03:54,633
Hello?

52
00:03:56,369 --> 00:03:58,303
Hello?

53
00:04:00,039 --> 00:04:02,633
Ha! Prepare to die,
you mamaluke. Ow! Ooh!

54
00:04:02,709 --> 00:04:05,610
Ah! Hey! Hey!
[Grunts]

55
00:04:05,678 --> 00:04:08,169
- J-Man! You made it.
- Argyle, what are you doing?

56
00:04:08,248 --> 00:04:12,776
I'm sorry, J-Dog. You saw the door.
This is a dangerous business.

57
00:04:14,020 --> 00:04:15,954
And when you're the mac daddy
of private dicks...

58
00:04:16,022 --> 00:04:19,458
the flyin' monkeys- all they wanna do
is put you on the night train to Emerald City.

59
00:04:19,525 --> 00:04:23,962
You're lucky you didn't get your ticket punched,
Richard Dixon, private investigator.

60
00:04:24,030 --> 00:04:27,295
- Oh, no. I ain't Dick Dixon. I'm his partner.
- So why did you e-mail me?

61
00:04:27,367 --> 00:04:29,335
Why don't you get him to help you?

62
00:04:29,402 --> 00:04:31,962
Oh. Well, you see,
this ain't Double "D's" kind of gig.

63
00:04:32,038 --> 00:04:35,701
This is what we in the industry
call a "multifacetal" type thing.

64
00:04:35,775 --> 00:04:38,676
See, there's a lot of
cross-purposing entities, multicultural...

65
00:04:38,745 --> 00:04:41,043
purposes, you know-
all of that and what not.

66
00:04:41,114 --> 00:04:44,447
- Good-bye, Argyle.
- No, no, no! Wait! J-Dog. J-Dog.
You can't leave me.

67
00:04:44,517 --> 00:04:49,511
You can't leave. You're all I got, man.
I'm in trouble, Jarod. Please.

68
00:04:49,589 --> 00:04:53,992
[Jarod Narrating] Raymond Chandler
hada secret for writing detective stories.

69
00:04:54,060 --> 00:04:57,552
"When in doubt," he said,
"have somebody enter the room with a gun."

70
00:04:59,365 --> 00:05:02,493
Okay, it's an ice-cream cone.
But it was pistachio...

71
00:05:02,568 --> 00:05:04,968
and I'm allergic to pistachios.

72
00:05:05,038 --> 00:05:09,566
- You Dick Dixon?
- Me? No. I'm his partner. That's Dick Dixon.

73
00:05:11,411 --> 00:05:15,074
- Oh! Ow!
- Think that hurt? Taste this.

74
00:05:15,148 --> 00:05:17,514
[Jarod Narrating]
Let's call this story "Death by Double Dip."

75
00:05:17,583 --> 00:05:19,915
Now, our pistachio-packing
friend will have to wait...

76
00:05:19,986 --> 00:05:23,114
since the Pretender
is now Dick Dixon, private eye.

77
00:05:23,189 --> 00:05:27,023
Let me give you the skinny. Argyle's new job
was another epic work of fiction.

78
00:05:27,093 --> 00:05:29,755
Dick Dixon isn't even around anymore.

79
00:05:29,829 --> 00:05:32,457
He skipped town last year
buried in debt.

80
00:05:32,532 --> 00:05:35,228
Argyle had only become his partner
a week earlier.

81
00:05:35,301 --> 00:05:38,202
He was working the building
as a "hospitality technician."

82
00:05:38,271 --> 00:05:41,707
And that's what he called it.
I call it "janitor."

83
00:05:41,774 --> 00:05:46,734
He happened to be scrubbing Dick Dixon's
abandoned office when... she walked in.

84
00:05:46,813 --> 00:05:48,747
I'm looking for Dick?

85
00:05:50,783 --> 00:05:52,774
Excuse me?

86
00:05:54,687 --> 00:05:57,417
- You know- Dick.
- Dick?

87
00:05:57,490 --> 00:06:01,722
- Dick Dixon?
- Oh. Oh. Dick Dixon.

88
00:06:01,794 --> 00:06:05,252
Uh, yeah.
Um, no. He's gone.

89
00:06:05,331 --> 00:06:07,526
- Gone?
- Yeah. He took the slow boat to China.

90
00:06:07,600 --> 00:06:09,591
[Spoken Lyric]
...that kind of thing.

91
00:06:09,669 --> 00:06:11,694
- Do you work for him?
- Do I work for him?

92
00:06:11,771 --> 00:06:15,935
- Yeah.
- Do I work for him? I am his nom de plume.

93
00:06:16,008 --> 00:06:19,102
I'm his coup de grace. I am
his comrade-in-arms, you know what I'm sayin'?

94
00:06:19,178 --> 00:06:23,615
- I am his partner, for Pete's sake.
- Um, you do his dirty work?

95
00:06:23,683 --> 00:06:27,050
That's funny.
This mop- you see- I'm undercover.

96
00:06:27,120 --> 00:06:30,487
I'm what we in the industry
call the "clandestinal" partner.

97
00:06:30,556 --> 00:06:33,320
Whatever Dick wants, Argyle gets Dick.

98
00:06:33,393 --> 00:06:36,123
"Argyle." That's an interesting name.

99
00:06:36,195 --> 00:06:38,891
Yeah. My parents gave it to me
on account of my birthmark.

100
00:06:38,965 --> 00:06:41,832
Hey, would you like to see
my birthmark?

101
00:06:41,901 --> 00:06:45,064
- No.
- Oh, no. I'm sorry. I-

102
00:06:45,138 --> 00:06:48,574
- [Sobs]
- I get that a lot. Please don't cry.
I hate to see a girl cry.

103
00:06:48,641 --> 00:06:53,169
Here. Take this. There you go.
That's all right.

104
00:06:53,246 --> 00:06:55,612
- Say, what's your name?
- Mona.

105
00:06:55,681 --> 00:06:58,616
- Like the Lisa?
- Yeah.

106
00:06:58,684 --> 00:07:01,653
- That's very beautiful.
- [Blows Nose Loudly]

107
00:07:02,889 --> 00:07:06,347
Listen, Mona. I can help.
Talk to me.

108
00:07:07,760 --> 00:07:12,959
Well, I'm a showgirl
down at the Club Ali Bar...

109
00:07:13,032 --> 00:07:16,001
and my boss is in trouble.

110
00:07:16,068 --> 00:07:18,696
Trouble?
What's your boss's name?

111
00:07:18,771 --> 00:07:20,830
- Dirty Willy.
- He doesn't bathe?

112
00:07:20,907 --> 00:07:23,671
No. People just call him that.

113
00:07:23,743 --> 00:07:29,147
He's a good man, takes care of us,
and all the girls have comprehensive dental.

114
00:07:29,215 --> 00:07:34,881
- Wow. That's key.
- And this bucket of quarters 
is all he's got left.

115
00:07:34,954 --> 00:07:40,483
And he told me to give this
to Mr. Dixon.

116
00:07:40,560 --> 00:07:42,824
Okay.

117
00:07:42,895 --> 00:07:46,991
I will get this to Mr. Dixon.

118
00:07:47,066 --> 00:07:51,025
- Willy knows things, Mr. Argyle-
- Oh, yeah?

119
00:07:51,103 --> 00:07:53,003
things that he shouldn't know.

120
00:07:53,072 --> 00:07:57,702
- He needs protection.
- Consider it done, Ms. Lisa.

121
00:07:57,777 --> 00:08:01,076
- Argyle is on the case.
- [Giggles]

122
00:08:02,281 --> 00:08:04,977
[Jarod Narrating]
"Argyle is on the case"-

123
00:08:05,051 --> 00:08:08,282
five words to send 
a chill down your spine.

124
00:08:08,354 --> 00:08:11,812
Argyle embraced the cliche,
casting himself in the starring role...

125
00:08:11,891 --> 00:08:15,054
of a big-time private eye extraordinaire.

126
00:08:15,127 --> 00:08:19,257
Determined to help Mona, he made 
his way back into the Club Ali Bar...

127
00:08:19,332 --> 00:08:21,732
and, like a true detective,
was looking for clues-

128
00:08:21,801 --> 00:08:25,760
anything he could find that would lead him
to where or what happened to Dirty Willy.

129
00:08:25,838 --> 00:08:28,306
But he wasn't ready to be a star.

130
00:08:28,374 --> 00:08:33,277
As soon as things got real,
Argyle wished he'd taken a bit part.

131
00:08:36,616 --> 00:08:38,607
[Argyle Gasps]
Dirty Willy.

132
00:08:38,684 --> 00:08:42,552
He'd done the job, solved the case.
He had the killer cornered.

133
00:08:42,622 --> 00:08:45,022
- So Argyle did what Argyle does best.
- [Gasps]

134
00:08:45,091 --> 00:08:48,857
- He never saw the hit man.
Who could at that speed?
- Woah!

135
00:08:48,928 --> 00:08:53,797
He was pretty sure the killer 
didn't see him- pretty sure.

136
00:08:53,866 --> 00:08:57,029
Which brings us back
to our pistachio-packin 'porker.

137
00:08:57,103 --> 00:08:59,037
He was wondering
the same thing as me.

138
00:08:59,105 --> 00:09:01,266
- Where the hell is Mona?
- Well, I -I -I don't know.

139
00:09:01,340 --> 00:09:04,605
She told me she was comin' 
to see you, Dixon. And now she's gone?

140
00:09:04,677 --> 00:09:07,305
- Did she say where she was goin'?
- She hasn't told me anything.

141
00:09:07,380 --> 00:09:11,043
- Did she leave anything?
- Look. Normally, I don't talk
to gun-wielding thugs.

142
00:09:11,117 --> 00:09:16,077
Yeah. Your mama must be real proud
of you now, eh, big boy?

143
00:09:18,791 --> 00:09:20,725
No. She'd probably give me a lickin'.

144
00:09:22,028 --> 00:09:24,394
My mama's dead.

145
00:09:27,633 --> 00:09:31,125
Truth is, I'm not a thug.
My name is Mike. I'm Mona's brother.

146
00:09:31,203 --> 00:09:34,502
- Oh. Hi, Mike.
- Hi.

147
00:09:34,574 --> 00:09:38,340
[Sighs] It just ain't like her not to check in.
Our parents died when we were real little...

148
00:09:38,411 --> 00:09:40,572
and I made a promise to Mom
that I'd take care of Mona.

149
00:09:40,646 --> 00:09:45,015
- I just gotta know if she's okay.
- [Sighs]

150
00:09:45,084 --> 00:09:49,282
You will. Just as soon as we find out 
anything, you'll be the first to know.

151
00:09:49,355 --> 00:09:53,018
- I promise. Right, partner?
- Yeah.

152
00:09:53,092 --> 00:09:56,653
Dick Dixon is on the case,
kickin' tail and takin' names.

153
00:09:56,729 --> 00:10:01,393
You are Mr. Positivi-tivity, 
the Shah of "I Can." Hey, now. Swell ride.

154
00:10:01,467 --> 00:10:04,265
Like I always say,
private dick's gotta have a ragtop.

155
00:10:04,337 --> 00:10:06,703
- You are not going.
- What are you talkin' about?

156
00:10:06,772 --> 00:10:10,173
I am not a detective. You are not my partner.
If I'm going to help, you stay outta my way.

157
00:10:10,242 --> 00:10:13,109
That was extremely hostile.

158
00:10:13,179 --> 00:10:16,012
I can't keep saving your life
if you keep lying yourself into a corner.

159
00:10:16,082 --> 00:10:18,573
- You have to think.
- [Engine Starts]
- Hey!

160
00:10:18,651 --> 00:10:20,585
- [Engine Stops]
- I've been thinkin'.

161
00:10:20,653 --> 00:10:23,520
I was-
[Spoken Lyric] till I met you.

162
00:10:23,589 --> 00:10:28,526
Now after you helped me and Pop last year,
I'm mendin' my wicked ways, you know.

163
00:10:28,594 --> 00:10:31,290
I ain't had nothin'
but honest jobs since.

164
00:10:31,364 --> 00:10:36,563
Only thing missin' is the love of my life.
And I met her last week.

165
00:10:43,743 --> 00:10:48,203
- Mona's the one.
- You spent six minutes with her.

166
00:10:48,280 --> 00:10:53,741
360 glorious seconds, J-Man.
Somethin' happened between us, I'm tellin' ya.

167
00:10:53,819 --> 00:10:57,186
It was like "electronical" chemicals
or something.

168
00:10:57,256 --> 00:10:59,190
Pheromones, baby,
I'm tellin' ya.

169
00:10:59,258 --> 00:11:02,318
And now my future brother-in-law's
weepin' in his pistachio.

170
00:11:02,395 --> 00:11:05,364
You gotta let me come with you, J-ster.
You gotta let me help her.

171
00:11:05,431 --> 00:11:08,195
J-Man. J-Dog.
Please, I'm beggin' ya.

172
00:11:08,267 --> 00:11:10,292
Please, please, please,
please, please.

173
00:11:10,369 --> 00:11:14,169
There are certain times in life when you need
to think with your heart, not your head.

174
00:11:14,240 --> 00:11:19,371
This wasn't one of those times, but I thought
it was, so I made the following mistake.

175
00:11:19,445 --> 00:11:22,937
- Please?
- Get in.

176
00:11:23,015 --> 00:11:25,848
Yeah, yeah.

177
00:11:25,918 --> 00:11:29,046
- [Engine Starts]
- Argyle is on the case. Come on!

178
00:11:34,860 --> 00:11:37,920
How did I get in this nightmare?

179
00:11:37,997 --> 00:11:41,398
Well, I-I remember
I was watching out for Jarod...

180
00:11:41,467 --> 00:11:45,961
and you looked at me with bedroom eyes,
like you wanted to do the late-night creep.

181
00:11:46,038 --> 00:11:49,405
I did not. We did not.

182
00:11:49,475 --> 00:11:52,035
Well, how can you be sure,
Miss Parker?

183
00:11:52,111 --> 00:11:54,841
For starters, pigs aren't flying,
hell hasn't frozen over...

184
00:11:54,914 --> 00:11:57,712
and you're not the last man on earth.

185
00:11:57,783 --> 00:12:01,150
[Rings]

186
00:12:01,220 --> 00:12:03,745
- What?
- How's the stakeout going?

187
00:12:03,823 --> 00:12:06,053
Sydney, how are you?

188
00:12:07,727 --> 00:12:09,661
I... am fine.

189
00:12:10,796 --> 00:12:12,957
Sweeper team says you haven't reported in.

190
00:12:13,032 --> 00:12:15,125
Huh. Something came up.

191
00:12:15,201 --> 00:12:19,900
I... overslept, but-
but I was just getting dressed.

192
00:12:19,972 --> 00:12:22,805
I'll be there tomorrow
with Lyle and Raines.

193
00:12:22,875 --> 00:12:25,639
Parker, is everything all right?

194
00:12:25,711 --> 00:12:28,578
I am rolling nothing but sevens.
[Chuckles]

195
00:12:38,657 --> 00:12:42,753
[Quietly]
You so much as hint at this 
when they arrive...

196
00:12:42,828 --> 00:12:46,286
I will amputate your head.

197
00:12:46,365 --> 00:12:50,301
- Well, what about this?
- There is no "this."

198
00:12:50,369 --> 00:12:52,667
Nothing happened, Broots.

199
00:12:52,738 --> 00:12:57,471
Like I said, it was a nightmare,
and I'm glad I woke up.

200
00:12:57,543 --> 00:13:00,706
When you say things like that,
do you even consider my feelings?

201
00:13:03,482 --> 00:13:05,780
What is it about me
that you find so repulsive?

202
00:13:07,853 --> 00:13:10,822
- You really want to know?
- Yes. I really want to know.

203
00:13:10,890 --> 00:13:13,017
Okay.

204
00:13:13,092 --> 00:13:16,357
Now you shut up and listen.

205
00:13:17,563 --> 00:13:22,432
What I find so utterly uninspiring
about you...

206
00:13:22,501 --> 00:13:25,561
is your idea of risk
is to go without deodorant.

207
00:13:25,638 --> 00:13:30,701
When the bullets stop flying,
you're always the one shaking in the corner.

208
00:13:30,776 --> 00:13:35,873
That, in the game of life,
is second string.

209
00:13:35,948 --> 00:13:39,645
And-
[Spoken Lyric]

210
00:13:39,718 --> 00:13:44,815
Hey. Stop, and let me tell
you something, and you-

211
00:13:44,890 --> 00:13:47,688
you shut up and listen.

212
00:13:47,760 --> 00:13:50,593
You're right.

213
00:13:50,663 --> 00:13:54,224
I have never taken a risk.

214
00:13:54,300 --> 00:13:57,531
Because the whole time I've known you,
I've only wanted to take just one.

215
00:13:57,603 --> 00:14:00,231
