00:28:42,785 --> 00:28:44,912
A reservation
doesn't mean he's gonna show.

435
00:28:44,987 --> 00:28:46,921
- We're leaving.
- We're staying.

436
00:28:47,923 --> 00:28:50,585
Did he just ignore us?

437
00:28:50,659 --> 00:28:53,753
You wanna barge in here
and try and scare me? You go ahead.

438
00:28:53,829 --> 00:28:59,768
But don't question my skills. 
I'm not second string anymore. 
I do a job, and I do it well.

439
00:28:59,835 --> 00:29:03,896
And if your paranoid minds can't take that,
then you can go chase that photo.

440
00:29:03,972 --> 00:29:06,202
Miss Parker and I will catch Jarod.

441
00:29:14,316 --> 00:29:16,511
Enjoy your breakfast.

442
00:29:17,953 --> 00:29:20,945
[Wheels Squeaking]

443
00:29:29,665 --> 00:29:32,498
You better hope we catch Jarod,
or we're through.

444
00:29:32,568 --> 00:29:34,559
- You mean us?
- I mean our necks.

445
00:29:39,108 --> 00:29:41,338
[Jarod Narrating]
As Argyle and I drove back to Benny's...

446
00:29:41,410 --> 00:29:45,107
we knew that without the mysterious
Frost Brothers, there was no Mona...

447
00:29:45,180 --> 00:29:48,274
and no dream for Argyle.

448
00:29:48,350 --> 00:29:51,649
But Argyle 's dream
wasn't the only one in jeopardy.

449
00:29:51,720 --> 00:29:55,247
- Oh, those bastards. Bastards, all of them!
- Benny, what happened?

450
00:29:55,324 --> 00:29:58,384
There I am.
I am standing there in the bunker.

451
00:29:58,460 --> 00:30:01,793
I am halfway into my "overature,"
and they grab me.

452
00:30:01,864 --> 00:30:04,765
- Wayne's bodyguards.
- Oh, bite your tongue. Wayne's people...

453
00:30:04,833 --> 00:30:07,324
would never do that with a rake.

454
00:30:07,402 --> 00:30:11,031
Ah, it was those lowlifes that work for
the other half of Wayne's threesome-

455
00:30:11,106 --> 00:30:13,666
those "mugicians" with the big hair?

456
00:30:13,742 --> 00:30:16,440
It's a good thing
they didn't bring their tigers, boy.

457
00:30:16,573 --> 00:30:19,906
- Whew.
- So Wayne never heard your song?

458
00:30:19,976 --> 00:30:24,242
No. And I know he would've loved it.
He would've loved it.

459
00:30:24,314 --> 00:30:26,475
Of course he would have.

460
00:30:26,550 --> 00:30:29,713
- What's the matter with him?
- We haven't found Mona yet.

461
00:30:29,786 --> 00:30:35,452
Oh, boy. Oh, boy.
It's always a girl, isn't it?

462
00:30:36,927 --> 00:30:39,361
Let me let you in
on a little tiny secret.

463
00:30:39,429 --> 00:30:41,363
He's just exactly like me.

464
00:30:41,431 --> 00:30:46,459
- No.
- Oh, yes. I was wild. I was unchecked...

465
00:30:46,536 --> 00:30:48,800
until my Adella tamed me.

466
00:30:48,872 --> 00:30:53,502
I still remember that trip to Vegas.
We wanted to get away from it all.

467
00:30:53,577 --> 00:30:58,344
Dr. Kanapa had told us that 
we wouldn't be able to have a family...

468
00:30:58,415 --> 00:31:01,816
and I know it was really tough for her.

469
00:31:01,885 --> 00:31:03,819
But my Adella-

470
00:31:03,887 --> 00:31:07,983
God, she looked so beautiful
the night we went to see Wayne.

471
00:31:08,058 --> 00:31:13,121
Ya never saw a polka dot dress
like that in your life.

472
00:31:13,196 --> 00:31:15,824
Well, big Wayne-

473
00:31:15,899 --> 00:31:19,995
he picks her out of the whole crowd...

474
00:31:20,070 --> 00:31:24,769
and he sang "Danke Schoen" right to her.

475
00:31:24,841 --> 00:31:27,332
- It was-
- Like a dream.

476
00:31:27,410 --> 00:31:33,349
Yeah. That night,
Adella came back to the motor court...

477
00:31:33,416 --> 00:31:35,714
all giddy from Wayne's show, you know?

478
00:31:35,785 --> 00:31:41,417
And we drove the cattle across the prairie
all night long, if you catch my meaning...

479
00:31:43,159 --> 00:31:45,889
and... we were blessed.

480
00:31:45,962 --> 00:31:50,729
- You conceived Argyle.
- Rolled a hard eight. [Chuckles]

481
00:31:50,800 --> 00:31:53,997
- [Benny] So now, when I see him
goin'through all this-
- [Dog Whimpers]

482
00:31:54,070 --> 00:31:58,939
I think, "Where would I be today
if it weren't for my Adella?"

483
00:32:00,176 --> 00:32:02,110
She was your Mona.

484
00:32:04,047 --> 00:32:06,743
[Sighs]
Jarod...

485
00:32:06,816 --> 00:32:10,650
ya gotta find that girl for my boy.

486
00:32:11,721 --> 00:32:13,655
[Dog Whimpers]

487
00:32:15,559 --> 00:32:18,221
[Jarod Narrating]
It seems everybody who met Mona wanted her:

488
00:32:18,295 --> 00:32:20,957
Argyle, her brother, Falzone.

489
00:32:21,031 --> 00:32:23,295
It got my detective gears spinning.

490
00:32:23,366 --> 00:32:26,961
Look, buddy boy.
I followed her home once- okay, twice.

491
00:32:27,037 --> 00:32:31,440
Nick had known everything about Mona:
where she lived, how she saved her money.

492
00:32:31,508 --> 00:32:33,499
Maybe he knew
who the Frost Brothers were.

493
00:32:33,577 --> 00:32:37,240
- But I swear, I never heard of 
the Frost Brothers.
- It was almost a dead end.

494
00:32:37,314 --> 00:32:39,248
- Almost.
- Dixon.

495
00:32:39,316 --> 00:32:43,275
Deputy Wyatt hadn't punched me 
the first time we met. 
Guess he figured I was due.

496
00:32:43,353 --> 00:32:47,983
- Oh, this is gettin' really old.
- You tryin' to destroy three months
of real police work?

497
00:32:48,058 --> 00:32:50,583
- We almost got Falzone for extortion.
- So get him.

498
00:32:50,660 --> 00:32:52,958
After you talked to him?
You of all people should know...

499
00:32:53,029 --> 00:32:55,827
there's only one way
to do things in this town: the Vegas way.

500
00:32:55,899 --> 00:32:58,424
What about the Frost Brothers way?

501
00:32:58,501 --> 00:33:00,628
- What's that place got to do with anything?
- Place?

502
00:33:00,704 --> 00:33:02,296
- Place?
- Place?

503
00:33:02,372 --> 00:33:07,002
Place. It's an abandoned meat-packing plant
outside town. So what?

504
00:33:11,181 --> 00:33:14,150
[Dog Barking, Whimpers]

505
00:33:17,954 --> 00:33:21,788
Mona?
Mona?

506
00:33:21,858 --> 00:33:24,952
[Whimpering, Barks]

507
00:33:26,029 --> 00:33:27,963
Mona?

508
00:33:31,034 --> 00:33:33,935
Mona! Mona!

509
00:33:34,971 --> 00:33:38,498
- Mona.
- I didn't think you'd come.

510
00:33:38,575 --> 00:33:42,841
- Oh, you're so cold. 
L-Let's get you out of here.
- Argyle, these two guys-

511
00:33:42,912 --> 00:33:44,903
They had masks on.
They grabbed me.

512
00:33:44,981 --> 00:33:48,007
They've been trying to get me to tell them
what Dirty Willy told me.

513
00:33:48,084 --> 00:33:51,679
But I can't tell them that secret,
'cause I can't do that to Willy.

514
00:33:51,755 --> 00:33:54,519
- Well, you could tel I us the secret, Mona.
- Tell us later.

515
00:33:54,591 --> 00:33:56,218
We have to get out of here right now.

516
00:33:56,292 --> 00:33:58,692
Yeah. We need to get you back
to your brother.

517
00:33:58,762 --> 00:34:01,094
Brother?
I don't have a brother.

518
00:34:01,164 --> 00:34:04,156
- Sure you do. Two of'em.
- [Barks]

519
00:34:04,234 --> 00:34:08,398
- [Dog Growling]
- Argyle, say hello to the Frost Brothers.

520
00:34:08,471 --> 00:34:13,204
[Continues Growling]

521
00:34:19,949 --> 00:34:22,850
[Jarod Narrating]
It was a case to make Ray Chandler proud.

522
00:34:22,919 --> 00:34:26,719
Let's review.
Our two sheriff deputies, Wyatt and Mike...

523
00:34:26,790 --> 00:34:31,318
they killed Dirty Willy-
tortured him, froze him, hung him.

524
00:34:31,394 --> 00:34:35,524
But what did they want out of him?
Money? Do-re-mi?

525
00:34:35,598 --> 00:34:38,226
- You won't be surprised
if I tell you the answer is no.
- [Whimpers]

526
00:34:38,301 --> 00:34:41,566
Dirty Willy had
one dirty little secret left...

527
00:34:41,638 --> 00:34:45,074
and these guys were trying
to get it out of Mona... and us.

528
00:34:45,141 --> 00:34:48,872
- It's been eight hours. Start talking.
- I got nothin' to say.

529
00:34:48,945 --> 00:34:52,904
You just don't get it, do you, Dixon?
We do things the Vegas way.

530
00:34:52,982 --> 00:34:56,509
Now, Mona's brother here
is gonna drive her into the desert.

531
00:34:56,586 --> 00:35:01,387
If he doesn't hear from me in 30,
she's gone, and I ice the two of you.

532
00:35:03,893 --> 00:35:07,659
- Oh, and I keep the dog.
- [Growling Continues]

533
00:35:07,731 --> 00:35:10,928
Don't give 'em anything, Argyle.
Not one quarter!

534
00:35:12,702 --> 00:35:15,227
- [Barking]
- Ah, put a sock in it, Dog.

535
00:35:15,305 --> 00:35:17,239
That was a strange thing to say.

536
00:35:17,307 --> 00:35:19,798
Yeah, right-
especially since dogs don't wear socks.

537
00:35:19,876 --> 00:35:23,937
Not Dog. Mona. She said, "not a quarter."
"Don't give them one quarter."

538
00:35:24,013 --> 00:35:27,471
Well, J-Man, Mona left a bucket 
full of quarters in Dick Dixon's office.

539
00:35:27,550 --> 00:35:32,078
Dirty Willy's secret. Whatever he was tryin'
to protect must have been in that bucket.

540
00:35:32,155 --> 00:35:35,420
- Wyatt!
- Hey, what the hell are you doin'?

541
00:35:35,492 --> 00:35:38,586
I'm gonna give him what he wants.
Wyatt!

542
00:35:47,237 --> 00:35:50,331
- There it is.
- [Beeps]

543
00:35:50,406 --> 00:35:52,806
[Wyatt On Tape]
Look, Willy. If you pay us what we need...

544
00:35:52,876 --> 00:35:55,504
we won't need to get rough with you.
[Beeps]

545
00:35:55,578 --> 00:35:58,706
Falzone wasn't extorting money
from Willy and his club. You were.

546
00:35:58,782 --> 00:36:00,682
And the dirty fat boy
recorded me doin' it.

547
00:36:00,750 --> 00:36:05,153
- All the time you just wanted that tape,
it was right there.
- Nice work, detectives.

548
00:36:05,221 --> 00:36:07,553
Willy was just tryin' to get that tape
to Dick Dixon.

549
00:36:07,624 --> 00:36:10,115
So now you got it.
Call your deputy and let Mona go.

550
00:36:10,193 --> 00:36:13,526
Poor Willy didn't even know
that Dick Dixon had skipped town.

551
00:36:13,596 --> 00:36:17,123
Wait a second.
You're not Dick Dixon?

552
00:36:18,968 --> 00:36:22,335
- No.
- [Slot Machine Bell Ringing]

553
00:36:22,405 --> 00:36:25,704
- [Ice Pick Tapping On Desk]
- Loser.

554
00:36:25,775 --> 00:36:28,209
[Tapping Continues]

555
00:36:28,278 --> 00:36:30,803
[Groaning]

556
00:36:30,880 --> 00:36:32,871
Oh, hi, there.

557
00:36:33,950 --> 00:36:36,248
- Let me outta this.
- Uh-uh.

558
00:36:36,319 --> 00:36:38,981
- You know, you should be protecting people-
- [Slot Machine Clicking]

559
00:36:39,055 --> 00:36:40,989
not extorting from them.

560
00:36:41,057 --> 00:36:43,548
But I guess that's what they call
the "Vegas way," right?

561
00:36:43,626 --> 00:36:46,026
- Oh, yeah.
- Well, we've already tried that.

562
00:36:46,095 --> 00:36:48,325
- Let's try the Jarod way.
- No! No! No!

563
00:36:49,766 --> 00:36:52,234
- You're totally whacked.
- You don't know the half of it.

564
00:36:52,302 --> 00:36:56,568
- You're going to make a call.
You're going to let Mona go.
- I don't think so.

565
00:36:56,639 --> 00:36:58,698
- Loser.
- [Sighs]

566
00:36:58,775 --> 00:37:01,710
- [Wyatt Yelps]
- Oh. Ooh, that's harder than golf.

567
00:37:01,778 --> 00:37:03,678
- You're outta your mind.
- Make the call.

568
00:37:03,746 --> 00:37:05,543
- No.
- Uh, loser.

569
00:37:09,786 --> 00:37:13,347
- Last chance.
- [Breathing Heavily]

570
00:37:13,423 --> 00:37:16,392
- Loser.
- Okay.

571
00:37:18,461 --> 00:37:21,521
- Fore!
- [Jarod Narrating] Wyatt finally made the call.

572
00:37:21,598 --> 00:37:25,466
And so did I- to the F..B.I.

573
00:37:25,535 --> 00:37:28,504
When they arrived at the office,
they found a killer waiting for them...

574
00:37:28,571 --> 00:37:30,732
along with the evidence
to convict him-

575
00:37:30,807 --> 00:37:33,799
all courtesy of the mysterious
Richard W. Dixon.

576
00:37:34,410 --> 00:37:36,344
But the story isn't over.

577
00:37:36,412 --> 00:37:38,880
I still have one more job to do.

578
00:37:40,383 --> 00:37:42,749
Anything?

579
00:37:42,819 --> 00:37:44,753
Nothing.

580
00:37:44,821 --> 00:37:49,554
Which is what we're gonna be
when we get back to the Centre.

581
00:37:49,626 --> 00:37:54,290
It was fun while it lasted-
[Whispering] Puff Daddy.

582
00:37:57,967 --> 00:38:01,232
[Faucet Turns, Water Running]

583
00:38:06,376 --> 00:38:08,344
Miss-

584
00:38:13,182 --> 00:38:17,278
Hoo. I guess I'm not a scrub anymore.

585
00:38:18,988 --> 00:38:22,856
I hope you like Renewal Wing,
'cause I'm gettin' you a gift certificate.

586
00:38:22,926 --> 00:38:27,022
The Centre reeducators can wipe
this entire weekend from your brain.

587
00:38:27,096 --> 00:38:31,556
[Jarod]
Well, you better tell them 
that Broots caught me.

588
00:38:34,070 --> 00:38:36,538
[Chuckles]

589
00:38:39,375 --> 00:38:43,311
Don't have to.
We're a team, aren't we...

590
00:38:43,379 --> 00:38:45,438
Dr. Funkenstein?

591
00:38:45,515 --> 00:38:48,609
Well, that all depends
on one thing, baby.

592
00:38:48,685 --> 00:38:51,813
Am I your Puff Daddy?

593
00:38:55,058 --> 00:38:59,358
[Sighs]
Oh, yeah, baby.

594
00:38:59,429 --> 00:39:03,991
And I wanna get funked up.

595
00:39:06,703 --> 00:39:09,672
Oh, I have to watch?

596
00:39:11,174 --> 00:39:13,165
You get to watch.

597
00:39:13,242 --> 00:39:15,506
[Both Giggle]

598
00:39:15,578 --> 00:39:19,070
I'll tell you what, Mr. Funkadelic.

599
00:39:19,148 --> 00:39:23,209
If we're gonna do this,
let's do it right.

600
00:39:24,220 --> 00:39:26,518
It's my turn to live out a fantasy.

601
00:39:26,589 --> 00:39:31,754
- Bald men have always driven me crazy.
- [Broots Chuckles]

602
00:39:31,828 --> 00:39:36,060
- # [Chorus Singing Slow Soul]
- And it takes more than one 
to really satisfy me.

603
00:39:36,132 --> 00:39:39,033
- Mr. Wiggles, get in here!
- # [Continues]

604
00:39:39,102 --> 00:39:41,297
[Wheels Squeaking]

605
00:39:46,976 --> 00:39:49,706
[Spoken Lyric]

606
00:39:49,779 --> 00:39:53,840
# [Continues]

607
00:39:58,354 --> 00:40:00,720
No.

608
00:40:02,825 --> 00:40:05,259
Miss Parker, what about us?

609
00:40:05,328 --> 00:40:08,297
[Spoken Lyric]

610
00:40:08,364 --> 00:40:10,696
No.

611
00:40:10,767 --> 00:40:13,065
No.

612
00:40:13,136 --> 00:40:16,867
No. No.

613
00:40:16,939 --> 00:40:19,100
No!

614
00:40:19,175 --> 00:40:23,703
What the- Ah! Mr. Wiggles.
[Sputters] Ow.

615
00:40:23,780 --> 00:40:26,078
I told you not to fall asleep.

616
00:40:26,149 --> 00:40:28,583
- I was asleep?
- Yeah.

617
00:40:29,652 --> 00:40:32,644
- The whole time?
- Yes, Rip Van Winkle.

618
00:40:32,722 --> 00:40:36,214
You were makin'
some weird noises too.

619
00:40:36,292 --> 00:40:41,059
And by the way, what exactly
is a "Puff Daddy"?

620
00:40:54,610 --> 00:40:57,875
[Jarod Narrating]
Like I said, I have one more thing to do.

621
00:40:57,947 --> 00:41:01,007
But it isn't this... dream.

622
00:41:01,084 --> 00:41:03,245
- It's somebody else's.
- [Strains]

623
00:41:08,591 --> 00:41:11,526
- Can I help you with that?
- Why, I-

624
00:41:12,728 --> 00:41:15,288
- [Chuckling]
- Oh, God. Oh, God.

625
00:41:15,364 --> 00:41:20,961
If you knew, sir, how much I've wanted 
to meet- This is an honor, sir.

626
00:41:21,037 --> 00:41:26,168
- This is an honor.
- Listen. Third row, polka dot dress.

627
00:41:26,242 --> 00:41:28,540
- Sir?
- Adella.

628
00:41:28,611 --> 00:41:32,638
- She was wearin' a polka dot dress.
- You are a god.

629
00:41:32,715 --> 00:41:38,278
[Chuckles] Listen. I understand
there's something you'd like me to hear.

630
00:41:38,354 --> 00:41:41,790
- Well, as a matter of fact, uh,
you probably wouldn't wanna-
- # [Accordion: Stray Notes]

631
00:41:41,858 --> 00:41:43,621
- You know-
- I'd love to.

632
00:41:43,693 --> 00:41:45,183
- You would?
- I would.

633
00:41:45,261 --> 00:41:47,388
- Yeah? [Chuckles]
- # [Stray Notes]

634
00:41:47,463 --> 00:41:50,864
Okay. Here we go.

635
00:41:50,933 --> 00:41:54,801
# [Swing Introduction]

636
00:41:54,871 --> 00:41:57,499
# AufWiedersehen, baby #

637
00:41:57,573 --> 00:42:01,805
# AufWiedersehen #

638
00:42:01,878 --> 00:42:04,346
# It means good-bye, my baby#

639
00:42:04,413 --> 00:42:08,144
# I don't know why
I feel this pain #

640
00:42:08,217 --> 00:42:10,549
# It's not my goiter #

641
00:42:10,620 --> 00:42:13,748
# But let's reconnoiter #

642
00:42:13,823 --> 00:42:18,487
# So even though I'm on that 
far-off desert in Morocco #

643
00:42:18,561 --> 00:42:21,826
- # I'm feelin' rocko, 
but I wanna do this refrain #
- [Howls]

644
00:42:21,898 --> 00:42:24,765
# AufWiedersehen #

645
00:42:24,834 --> 00:42:27,598
- # AufWiedersehen ##
- # [Ends]

646
00:42:27,670 --> 00:42:30,104
- [Laughing]
- [Jarod, Argyle] Whoo!

647
00:42:33,442 --> 00:42:35,876
Well, that was unmistakablyyou.

648
00:42:35,945 --> 00:42:40,075
- That's just the first verse. 
There's more to come.
- I cannot wait.

649
00:42:40,149 --> 00:42:42,845
Uh, listen.
I wanna see you all tonight at my show.

650
00:42:42,919 --> 00:42:45,717
You'll be my guest.
I'll leave your names at the front door.

651
00:42:45,788 --> 00:42:51,522
And by the way, I want you to know
that Adella was my inspiration too.

652
00:42:51,594 --> 00:42:55,052
- Oh, thank you, sir. Thank you.
- See you. See you tonight.

653
00:42:56,432 --> 00:42:58,832
[Benny]
What a guy.

654
00:42:58,901 --> 00:43:01,267
- Thank you.
- My pleasure.

655
00:43:01,337 --> 00:43:04,431
That could be the worst song
I've ever heard.

656
00:43:04,507 --> 00:43:08,068
- I know. But to him it was a dream come true.
- [Chuckles]

657
00:43:08,144 --> 00:43:10,078
